    <prp:code></prp:code>
    <prp:abstract>Theoretical studies of  magnetized cores show that the process of magnetic braking 
makes it very difficult to form a circumstellar disk in the earliest stages of the 
collapse.  It is therefore important to detect, measure and map the magnetic field 
structure in the disk around a young stellar object. The SMA observations 
reported recently by us (Rao et al. 2014) of IRAS 16293-2422 B at 345 GHz are the 
first such measurements of the field structure in a face-on disk which shows a toroidal pattern.  
The SMA observations were hindered both by a lack of sensitivity and angular resolution 
which will be greatly improved by the ALMA observations. 

This proposal is a resubmission and continuation of an accepted ALMA Cycle2 proposal. We 
propose to extend the desired angular resolution to 0.08 arcseconds with 
the Band 7 Cycle 3 observations. The 
resolution achieved in Cycle 3 will vastly increase the number of mapped pixels
and will therefore be a significant improvement when trying to compare the observations
to the theoretical simulations. The magnetic field will be mapped on scales of 10 AU.
</prp:abstract>
